- Candidate 1 (close‑miked, vocal‑forward folk‑rock): directly matches the core singer‑songwriter preference for intimate, up‑front vocal miking and warm midrange lead vocals. The instrumentation (acoustic guitar, banjo, upright bass) and "organic live immediacy" align with minimal processing and analogue‑style character. The description emphasizes tasteful polish that preserves vocal character and "earnest dynamic builds" — this speaks to preserved dynamics, restrained arrangements and immersive storytelling/album flow rather than short, hook‑driven slices.
